Before installing anything

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
java --version
--> as its ubuntu, as its a debian packager, you need to install few pluggins in pkg.jenkins.io , we need those packages to install jenkin servers inside ubuntu instances
-->Ubuntu trusts Jenkins packages downloaded from pkg.jenkins.io
-->Run the following commands to add the Jenkins official repository:

curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee \
  /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null

-->once above command runt, it will add a key 
Then add the repository:

echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian binary/ | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

sudo apt-get update
  sudo apt-get install fontconfig openjdk-21-jre
  sudo apt-get install jenkins

-->Start and enable Jenkins service
sudo systemctl start jenkins
-->Enable it to start on boot:
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
-->status check
sudo systemctl status jenkins

